.TH RADON2CONFIG 1 "2026-05-02" "smartmet-tools-grid" "SmartMet GRID Tools"
.SH NAME
radon2config \- generate SmartMet GRID configuration files from a Radon database snapshot
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B radon2config
.I configDir
.I dbConnectionString
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B radon2config
reads geometry, producer and parameter definitions from FMI's internal
.B Radon
PostgreSQL database and writes the corresponding SmartMet GRID
configuration files into
.IR configDir .
The output files map FMI geometry identifiers to the geometries
recognised in GRIB and NetCDF files (\fIfmi_geometries.csv\fR and
related files).
.PP
The generated files are normally regenerated whenever the Radon
schema or contents change; they are not intended to be hand\(hyedited and
include a header that warns about this.
.PP
.B radon2config
is FMI\(hyspecific in that it requires a populated Radon database; sites
without Radon do not need it.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I configDir
Output directory for the generated configuration files. The directory
must already exist.
.TP
.I dbConnectionString
A libpq\(hystyle connection string for the Radon database, for example
.RI \(lq host=radon.fmi.fi " " dbname=radon " " user=u " " password=p \(rq.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR radon2smartmet (1),
.BR radon2csv (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Finnish Meteorological Institute
.PP
Report issues at <https://github.com/fmidev/smartmet-tools-grid/issues>.
